<paragraph id="8BED3694FFFD775B4AAEFCC437C3FDF9" blockId="5.[151,1437,153,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFFD775B4AAEFCC4345AFDB1" bold="true" box="[199,315,873,899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D17FFFD775B4864FCC73647FDB1" authorityName="ARROW" authorityYear="1901" box="[525,806,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bimaculatus" subSpecies="posticalis">
<emphasis id="B926EA86FFFD775B4864FCC73647FDB1" box="[525,806,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="70">P. bimaculatus posticalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elytral transverse band has united with the humeral spot and covers two-thirds of the elytra, the posterior third of elytra, the sutural line (expanded below the scutellum) and two vestiges below the humerus are black.
</paragraph>
